SUMMARY:🌳☕ ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE WALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE ☕
 🌳
DESCRIPTION:Try New Things in Toronto!\n🌳☕ **ST. CLAIR WEST VILLAGE W
 ALK\, WYCHWOOD PARK & COFFEE** ☕🌳\n\nHidden Streets\, Storybook Homes
  & A Cozy Café Finish\nSome parts of Toronto feel like you’ve accidenta
 lly stepped into another world.\n\nJoin us for a relaxed social walk throu
 gh **St. Clair West**\, leading into the quietly tucked-away and exclusive
  **Wychwood Park** — one of the city’s most unique residential enclave
 s.\n\nWychwood Park is private\, residential\, and unlike anywhere else in
  Toronto. The homes are all architecturally distinct — no cookie-cutter 
 builds here — and living there involves a waiting list\, a board approva
 l process\, and community guidelines that preserve its character. It feels
  almost village-like… peaceful\, artistic\, and slightly secret.\nThis i
 s not a formal historical tour.\nIt’s a social walk with beautiful surro
 undings and good conversation.\n\n👉 **Don’t forget to join our WhatsA
 pp group** – [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018gYANrK
 Anc?mode=ac_t)\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🚶‍♂️ **What We’ll Do**\n\nWe’l
 l begin by walking west along St. Clair\, enjoying the neighbourhood energ
 y before heading into Wychwood Park for a gentle wander through its windin
 g streets.\nAfterward\, we’ll make a short stop at **Artscape Wychwood B
 arns** to peek into the market space\, next we make a quick stop at Mr. Bi
 nz where everything starts at $25 and after we will head to **Bakery Garde
 n Cafe** for a warm drink and time to sit\, chat\, and connect.\nSometimes
  the best part of the walk is the pause at the end. ☕\nWe’ll eventuall
 y make our way back toward St. Clair Subway Station.\nYou’re welcome to 
 leave at any time.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n❄️ **Weather & Expectations**\n\nPl
 ease do not sign up if you’re not ready to walk in real winter condition
 s. This event will happen in snow\, cold\, or typical Toronto winter weath
 er.\nThe only exception: if temperatures reach -20°C\, the event will be 
 canceled.\nBundle up. Dress properly. This is a winter walk.\nAlso — thi
 s is NOT a historical tour. I’ll share context casually\, but the focus 
 is social connection and enjoying the neighbourhood.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🧢 
 Meetup Details\n📍 Meetup Location: Outside the station by McDonald’s\
 n🫎 I’ll be wearing my Moose Hat\n⏰ Meetup Time: 11:00 AM\nI will on
 ly wait 5 minutes.\nEarly is on time.\n\nOn time is late.\nWe will leave p
 romptly\, and I won’t be able to spend time trying to track people down 
 — thank you for respecting everyone’s time.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🎟️ **
 Meetup Fee:** $5 cash in person **or** e-transfer to\n📧 \\*\\*[mathewma
 clean@hotmail.com**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.com%2A%2A/)\nThis fee he
 lps support the group and allows us to keep hosting events like this. Than
 k you for supporting community! 💖\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n🎒 What to Bring\n\
 n* Water or a warm drink\n* Good walking shoes\n* A small snack\n* Warm cl
 othing (boots\, hat\, gloves — layers!)\n* Mask (if you prefer for indoo
 r stops)\n\nPlease also use the washroom before arriving\, as stops are li
 mited.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n📚 Learn More\nInterested in reading more about W
 ychwood Park before we go [Click Here](https://www.thestar.com/news/insigh
 t/2012/12/21/inside_the_weird_world_of_wychwood_park.html)?\n\n🌈 Who Is
  This For?\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to be social and make f
 riends — whether single or not.\n\nWe also host:\n🎬 Movies\n🚶 Walk
 s & hikes\n🎭 Arts & culture outings\n🍽️ Restaurant gatherings\nThe
 re’s always something happening.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\nREMEMBER: You’re welc
 ome to just show up on the day if you’re unsure about your schedule.\nAn
 d as always\, sometimes plans shift and events may need to be canceled —
  please keep an eye on updates.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\n👤 Organizer: Mathew\nQu
 estions? Post on the event wall or email\n📧 [torontomoviesandoutings@ho
 tmail.com](mailto:torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com)\n\nCome for the hid
 den streets. Stay for the cozy coffee.\nLeave feeling like you discovered 
 a pocket of the city most people never see.\nThere’s something special a
 bout wandering somewhere that feels quietly exclusive — especially when 
 you’re not wandering alone. 🌳✨
